---
import Layout from "../layouts/Layout.astro";
---

<Layout title="About" description="What ai-compat.info is and how the dataset is maintained.">
  <a href="/" class="back-link">← home</a>

  <section class="detail-card prose">
    <span class="eyebrow">About</span>
    <h1>What this is</h1>
    <p>
      `ai-compat.info` is a compact compatibility layer for AI models and the
      tools people actually drive them through: CLIs, editors, and autonomous
      runtimes.
    </p>
    <p>
      The site is opinionated on purpose. It treats pairings as products, not
      just benchmark numbers, so the scoring reflects workflow fit, developer
      ergonomics, and ecosystem maturity.
    </p>
  </section>

  <section class="grid cols-3" style="margin-top: 1rem;">
    <div class="section-card prose">
      <h2>How data is sourced</h2>
      <p>
        The shared dataset in `src/data/compat.json` is manually curated. Model
        capabilities, context windows, and harness descriptions are realistic
        summaries, then pair scores are seeded to reflect practical fit.
      </p>
    </div>
    <div class="section-card prose">
      <h2>How to contribute</h2>
      <p>
        Open a PR that updates the dataset, any affected ranking logic, and
        docs. Keep entries concrete, use consistent slugs, and explain the
        reasoning for any score changes.
      </p>
    </div>
    <div class="section-card prose">
      <h2>Credits</h2>
      <p>
        This repo ships an Astro site, a Go CLI, JSON API routes, and an
        OpenClaw skill scaffold that all read from the same compatibility file.
      </p>
    </div>
  </section>
</Layout>
